<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1328,1643]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,256,1328,1354]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Remark.</emphasis>
The species is known exclusively from female specimens. However, having compared the illustrations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,348,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odontographa">
<emphasis box="[151,348,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">M. odontographa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="in Hacker et al. (2012: 328" authorityName="in Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[402,828,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allardi">
<emphasis box="[402,515,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">M. allardi</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." box="[551,828,1364,1390]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref24228" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">
Hacker 
<emphasis box="[639,696,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">et al.</emphasis>
(2012: 328
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 427), it seems to be highly likely that the two species are conspecific. As the author of the present paper could not locate specimens of either species for thorough examination, both taxa have tentatively been treated here as valid. It is also worth mentioning that 
<taxonomicName authority="Hacker, 2012" authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inculta">
<emphasis box="[1228,1343,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">M. inculta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref24228" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">Hacker, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described from Katanga Province, D.R. Congo and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hacker, 2012" authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" box="[784,1129,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseodentata">
<emphasis box="[784,974,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">M. griseodentata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." box="[980,1129,1472,1498]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref24228" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">Hacker, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described from near 
<collectingRegion box="[1362,1432,1472,1498]" country="Tanzania" name="Iringa" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Iringa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,252,1508,1534]" name="Tanzania" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
are also confusingly similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[616,730,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allardi">
<emphasis box="[616,730,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">M. allardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both externally and in genital morphology. The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hacker" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inculta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">M. inculta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hacker, H. H. &amp; Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B." box="[380,658,1544,1570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="7 - 612" refId="ref24228" refString="Hacker, H. H., Schreier, H. P. &amp; Goater, B. (2012) Revision of the tribe Nolini of Africa and the Western Palaearctic Region (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Noctuidae, Nolinae). Esperiana, 17, 7 - 612." type="journal article" year="2012">
Hacker 
<emphasis box="[467,522,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">et al.</emphasis>
(2012: 332)
</bibRefCitation>
is misidentified and is in fact 
<taxonomicName authority="(van Son, 1933)" baseAuthorityName="van Son" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[987,1338,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Nolidae" genus="Meganola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monofascia">
<emphasis box="[987,1152,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">M. monofascia</emphasis>
(van 
<bibRefCitation author="Son, V. G." box="[1214,1330,1544,1570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="181 - 232" refId="ref24813" refString="Son, V. G. (1933) A revision of the South African moths of the tribe Nolini. Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 15 (2), 181 - 232." type="journal article" year="1933">Son, 1933</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In order to prove whether or not the four species are conspecific, examination of further material is necessary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
